[1]
Date: Fri 4 Apr 2008
From: Adolf Polivka
<adolf.polivka@utanet.at>


Measles outbreak in Austria
---------------------------
Up to now there have been about 180 cases of measles in Austria in and
around the city of Salzburg. (There have also been reports of measles
outbreaks in Germany (Bavaria) and Upper Austria). The [Salzburg] outbreak
began in a school, where most of the parents were against any immunisation
(a Waldorfschule).

--
Adolf Polivka
<adolf.polivka@utanet.at>

[ProMED-mail thanks Adolf Polivka for alerting us to this outbreak. - Mod.CP]

