[2]
Date: Wed 2 Apr 2008
Source: Federal Ministry of Health, Family and Youth, Press release
[machine translation, abbreviated and edited]
<http://www.bmgfj.gv.at/cms/site/presse_detail.html?channel=CH0616&doc=CMS1207138264557>


Measles outbreak in Salzburg
----------------------------
In relation to the accumulation of measles cases in Salzburg Health
Minister Dr Andrea Kdolsky today [2 Apr 2008] stated that appropriate
measures were being taken. Vaccine had been procured and made available. In
coordination with the Salzburg Governor's Office, the Minister of Health
from today will provide free vaccination for health care workers and Red
Cross personnel involved in containment of the the outbreak.

The Minister stressed that there are currently only around 120 cases to
handle. Therefore there is no cause for panic. Kdolsky stated, however,
that there was a need to raise and maintain high vaccination levels to
prevent future epidemics. He emphasized that it is important to raise the
level of vaccina acceptance to protect the whole community.

--
